text: Vest-Telemark is the name of an area, in the south of Norway . Some of the towns are: Fyresdal, Tokke, Vinje, Nissedal, Kviteseid, and Seljord. In no area, has one found more traces ( examples or evidence ) of the Old Norse language and grammar. Category:Geography of Norway Category:Telemark
title: Vest-Telemark
